Package org.eclipse.mosaic.lib.routing.database

Class DatabaseRouting

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.lib.routing.database.DatabaseRouting
All Implemented Interfaces:
VehicleRouting
public class DatabaseRouting extends Object implements VehicleRouting
An implementation of the VehicleRouting interface which provides access to routing functions based on data of the scenario-database.

    • approximateCostsForCandidateRoute

      public CandidateRoute approximateCostsForCandidateRoute(CandidateRoute route, String lastNodeId)
      Description copied from interface: VehicleRouting
      Approximates the costs of a CandidateRoute. Pass a CandidateRoute and the ID of the last Node the vehicle passed on to the method and it will return a new Candidate route with the approximated values in its "length" and "time" field. The method approximates by calculating distance and time between the candidate route's first intersection and last intersection. The calculation will be done on the fly and might thus have impact on overall performance of a simulation.
      Specified by:
      approximateCostsForCandidateRoute in interface VehicleRouting
      Parameters:
      route - CandidateRoute to be cost-approximated
      lastNodeId - ID of last passed node
      Returns:
      a new CandidateRoute
